014 as above}}\n| title1 = Fixing a Hole\n| note1 = Take 1\n| length1 = 3:00\n| title2 = Fixing a Hole\n| note2= Speech and Take 3\n| length2 = 3:28\n| title3 = Being for the Benefit of Mr. Kite!\n| note3= Speech from Before Take 1; Take 4 and Speech at the End\n| length3 = 3:08\n| title4 = Being for the Benefit of Mr. Kite!\n| note4= Take 7\n| length4 = 2:35\n| title5 = Lovely Rita\n| note5= Speech and Take 9\n| length5 = 3:05\n| title6 = Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\n| note6 = Take 1 and Speech at the End\n| length6 = 3:40\n| title7 = Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\n| note7 = Speech, False Start and Take 5\n| length7 = 4:08\n| title8 = Getting Better\n| note8 = Take 1 \u2013 Instrumental and Speech at the End\n| length8 = 2:19\n| title9 = Getting Better\n| note9 = Take 12\n| length9 = 2:45\n| title10 = Within You Without You\n| note10 = Take 1 \u2013 Indian Instruments Only\n| length10 = 5:33\n| title11 = Within You Without You\n| note11= George Coaching the Musicians\n| length11 = 3:56\n| title12 = She's Leaving Home\n| note12= Take 1 \u2013 Instrumental\n| length12 = 3:49\n| title13 = She's Leaving Home\n| note13= Take 6 \u2013 Instrumental\n| length13 = 3:48\n| title14 = With a Little Help from My Friends\n| note14 = Take 1 \u2013 False Start and Take 2 \u2013 Instrumental\n| length14 = 3:15\n| title15 = Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band (Reprise)\n| note15= Speech And Take 8\n| length15 = 2:00\n| total_length = 50:29\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = yes\n| headline = Super deluxe edition, disc four {{nobold|\u2014 1967 mono mix of original album (not listed) with 6 bonus tracks}}\n| title14 = Strawberry Fields Forever\n| note14 = Original Mono Mix\n| length14 = 4:08\n| title15 = Penny Lane\n| note15 = Original Mono Mix\n| length15 = 3:02\n| title16 = A Day in the Life\n| note16 = Unreleased First Mono Mix\n| length16 = 4:43\n| title17 = Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\n| note17 = Unreleased Mono Mix \u2013 No. 11\n| length17 = 3:49\n| title18 = She's Leaving Home\n| note18 = Unreleased First Mono Mix\n| length18 = 3:42\n| title19 = Penny Lane\n| note19 = Capitol Records U.S. Promo Single \u2013 Mono Mix\n| length19 = 3:01\n| total_length = 62:17\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\nAccording to Mark Lewisohn and Ian MacDonald:<ref>{{harvnb|Lewisohn|2010|pp=232\u2013253}}, {{harvnb|MacDonald|2005|pp=215\u2013250}}.</ref>\n\n'''The Beatles'''\n* [[John Lennon]] \u2013 lead, harmony and background vocals; rhythm, acoustic and lead guitars; [[Hammond organ]], final piano E chord; harmonica, [[tape loop]]s, [[sound effect]]s, [[comb and tissue paper]]; handclaps, tambourine, maracas\n* [[Paul McCartney]] \u2013 lead, harmony and background vocals; bass and lead guitars; electric and acoustic pianos, [[Lowrey organ|Lowrey]] and Hammond organs; handclaps; vocalisations, sound effects, comb and tissue paper\n* [[George Harrison]] \u2013 harmony and background vocals; lead, rhythm and acoustic guitars; [[sitar]], [[Tanpura|tambura]]; harmonica, comb and tissue paper; handclaps, maracas; lead vocals on \"Within You Without You\"\n* [[Ringo Starr]] \u2013 drums, [[conga]]s, [[tambourine]], [[maraca]]s, handclaps, [[tubular bells]]; lead vocals on \"With a Little Help from My Friends\"; harmonica; final piano E chord\n\n'''Additional musicians and production'''\n* [[Sounds Incorporated]] \u2013 the saxophone sextet on \"Good Morning Good Morning\"{{sfn|Emerick|Massey|2006|pp=176\u2013179}}\n* [[Neil Aspinall]] \u2013 tambura, harmonica{{sfn|MacDonald|2005|pp=237, 243}}\n* [[Geoff Emerick]] \u2013 [[audio engineering]]; tape loops, sound effects{{sfn|Emerick|Massey|2006|pp=132\u2013192}}{{refn|group=nb|Despite Martin's efforts to secure an engineer's credit for Emerick on ''Sgt. Pepper'', EMI refused the request based upon what was then company policy. While Peter Blake received a gold disc for his contribution to the album cover, Emerick did not receive one for his contribution to the album's recording, however; in 1968 he received a [[Grammy Award for Best Engineered Album, Non-Classical]].{{sfn|Emerick|Massey|2006|pp=191\u2013192}}}}\n* [[Mal Evans]] \u2013 counting, harmonica, alarm clock, final piano E chord{{sfn|MacDonald|2005|pp=227\u2013232, 237}}\n* [[George Martin]] \u2013 producer, [[audio mixing (recorded music)|mixer]]; tape loops, sound effects; [[harpsichord]] on \"Fixing a Hole\", [[Pump organ|harmonium]], Lowrey organ and [[glockenspiel]] on \"Being for the Benefit of Mr. Kite!\", Hammond organ on \"With a Little Help from My Friends\", piano on \"Getting Better\", piano solo on \"Lovely Rita\"; final harmonium chord.<ref>{{harvnb|Emerick|Massey|2006|p=171}}: piano solo on \"Lovely Rita\"; {{harvnb|MacDonald|2005|pp=235, 237, 246, 239, 241}}; {{harvnb|Womack|2007|p=180}}: final harmonium chord on \"A Day in the Life\".</ref>\n* Session musicians \u2013 four [[French horn]]s on \"Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band\": [[Neill Sanders]], James W. Buck, John Burden, Tony Randall,{{sfn|MacDonald|2005|p=232}} arranged and conducted by Martin and McCartney; [[string instrument|string]] section and harp on \"She's Leaving Home\", arranged by [[Mike Leander]] and conducted by Martin; [[tabla]], [[dilruba]]s, tamboura and [[swarmandal]] on \"Within You Without You\", played by members of the [[Asian Music Circle]], with eight violins and four cellos arranged and conducted by Harrison and Martin; clarinet trio on \"When I'm Sixty-Four\": Robert Burns, Henry MacKenzie, Frank Reidy, arranged and conducted by Martin and McCartney; saxophones on \"Good Morning Good Morning\", arranged and conducted by Martin and Lennon; and forty-piece [[orchestra]], including strings, [[brass instrument|brass]], [[woodwind instrument|woodwinds]] and [[percussion instrument|percussion]] on \"A Day in the Life\", arranged by Martin, Lennon and McCartney, and conducted by Martin and McCartney.<ref>{{harvnb|Emerick|Massey|2006|p=158}}: Martin and McCartney took turns conducting; {{harvnb|Gould|2007|pp=387\u2013388}}: the recording of \"A Day in the Life\" included a forty-piece orchestra; {{harvnb|Martin|Pearson|1994|p=35}}: Robert Burns, Henry MacKenzie, Frank Reidy.</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n=== Weekly charts ===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Original release\n|-\n!Chart\n!Position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Australian [[Kent Music Report]]<ref name=\"auchart\">{{Cite book|title=[[Kent Music Report|Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992]]|last=Kent|first=David|authorlink=David Kent (historian)|publisher=Australian Chart Book|location=[[St Ives, New South Wales|St Ives, NSW]]|year=1993|isbn=0-646-11917-6}}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Canadian [[RPM (magazine)|''RPM'' Top LPs]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.10081a&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.10081a.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.10081a |title=''RPM'' Top Albums/CDs \u2013 Volume 7, No. 21, Jul 22, 1967 |publisher=[[Library and Archives Canada]] |accessdate=8 April 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413012103/http://www.bac-lac.gc.ca/eng/discover/films-videos-sound-recordings/rpm/Pages/image.aspx?Image=nlc008388.10081a&URLjpg=http%3a%2f%2fwww.collectionscanada.gc.ca%2fobj%2f028020%2ff4%2fnlc008388.10081a.gif&Ecopy=nlc008388.10081a |archive-date=13 April 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Norwegian Albums Chart]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://norwegiancharts.com/weekchart.asp?year=1967&date=196724&cat=a |title=VG Lista \u2013 Album Top 40 |publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=16 November 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111229150911/http://norwegiancharts.com/weekchart.asp?year=1967&date=196724&cat=a |archive-date=29 December 2011 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Swedish [[Sverigetopplistan|Kv\u00e4llstoppen Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Swedish Charts 1966\u20131969/Kv\u00e4llstoppen \u2013 Listresultaten vecka f\u00f6r vecka > Juni 1967 > 20 Juni|url=http://www.hitsallertijden.nl/charts/swedish%20charts/SwedishCharts%200366-0969.pdf|work=hitsallertijden.nl|language=Swedish|accessdate=31 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305110338/http://www.hitsallertijden.nl/charts/swedish%20charts/SwedishCharts%200366-0969.pdf|archive-date=5 March 2018|url-status=live}}''Note: [[Sverigetopplistan|Kv\u00e4llstoppen]] combined sales for albums and singles in the one chart; ''Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band'' peaked at the number-five on the list on 20 June 1967''</ref>\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[UK Albums Chart]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/10363/beatles/|title=The Beatles \u2013 Full official Chart History|work=[[Official Charts]]|accessdate=13 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160512024604/http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/10363/beatles/|archive-date=12 May 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>{{sfn|Roberts|2005|p=54}}\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' Top LPs]]<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200?tag=chscr1#/charts/billboard-200?chartDate=1967-07-01 |title=Billboard 200 |work=Billboard |accessdate=16 November 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101115095520/http://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200?tag=chscr1#/charts/billboard-200?chartDate=1967-07-01 |archive-date=15 November 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|1\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Media Control|West German Media Control Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"dechart\">{{cite web|url = http://www.officialcharts.de/album.asp?artist=The+Beatles&title=Sgt.+Peppers+Lonely+Hearts+Club+Band&cat=a&country=de|title = Album Search: The Beatles \u2013 ''Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band''|language = German|publisher = Media Control|accessdate =1 May 2010|format=ASP}}</ref>\n|1\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+1987 reissue\n|-\n!Chart\n