{"title_page": "Enrico Mollo", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Enrico Mollo\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1913|7|24|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Turin]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|1992|3|10|1913|7|24|df=yes}}\n| death_place    = Turin, Italy\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n}}\n'''Enrico Mollo''' (24 July 1913 &ndash; 10 March 1992) was an Italian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. He won the 1935 edition of the [[Giro di Lombardia]].<ref name=\"ProCyclingStats\">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Enrico_Mollo |title=Enrico Mollo |accessdate=2 October 2015 |work=ProCyclingStats}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n;1935\n: 1st [[1935 Giro di Lombardia|Giro di Lombardia]]\n;1936\n: 1st [[Coppa Bernocchi]]\n: 2nd [[Giro del Lazio]]\n: 3rd [[Tre Valli Varesine]]\n: 9th Overall [[1936 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1937\n: 3rd Overall [[1937 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1938\n: 2nd [[Giro della Romagna]]\n: 3rd [[Giro dell'Umbria]]\n;1940\n: 2nd Overall [[1940 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1941\n: 2nd [[Giro dell'Umbria]]\n;1946\n: 1st [[Giro dell'Apennino]]\n: 1st [[Tre Valli Varesine]]\n: 1st [[Coppa Citt\u00e0 di Asti]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===General classification results timeline===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=9| Grand Tour general classification results\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Race\n! scope=\"col\" | 1936\n! scope=\"col\" | 1937\n! scope=\"col\" | 1938\n! scope=\"col\" | 1939\n! scope=\"col\" | 1940\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" |{{cjersey|pink}} [[General classification in the Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|'''[[1936 Giro d'Italia|9]]'''\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|'''[[1937 Giro d'Italia|3]]'''\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|'''[[1940 Giro d'Italia|2]]'''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | {{cjersey|yellow}} [[General classification in the Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|[[1938 Tour de France|38]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | {{cjersey|red}} [[List of Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a general classification winners|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Legend\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2014\n| Did not compete\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Did Not Finish|DNF]]\n| Did not finish\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|6124}}\n\n{{Giro di Lombardia winners |state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mollo, Enrico}}\n[[Category:1913 births]]\n[[Category:1992 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Turin]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-1910s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian cyclist}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Enrico Mollo\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1913|7|24|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Turin]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|1992|3|10|1913|7|24|df=yes}}\n| death_place    = Turin, Italy\n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      = \n| amateuryears1  = \n| amateurteam1   = \n| proyears1      = \n| proteam1       = \n| majorwins      = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n}}\n'''Enrico Mollo''' (24 July 1913 &ndash; 10 March 1992) was an Italian [[bicycle racing|racing cyclist]]. He won the 1935 edition of the [[Giro di Lombardia]].<ref name=\"ProCyclingStats\">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Enrico_Mollo |title=Enrico Mollo |accessdate=2 October 2015 |work=ProCyclingStats}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n;1935\n: 1st [[1935 Giro di Lombardia|Giro di Lombardia]]\n;1936\n: 1st [[Coppa Bernocchi]]\n: 2nd [[Giro del Lazio]]\n: 3rd [[Tre Valli Varesine]]\n: 9th Overall [[1936 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1937\n: 3rd Overall [[1937 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1938\n: 2nd [[Giro della Romagna]]\n: 3rd [[Giro dell'Umbria]]\n;1940\n: 2nd Overall [[1940 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n;1941\n: 2nd [[Giro dell'Umbria]]\n;1946\n: 1st [[Giro dell'Apennino]]\n: 1st [[Tre Valli Varesine]]\n: 1st [[Coppa Citt\u00e0 di Asti]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n===General classification results timeline===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" align=center colspan=9| Grand Tour general classification results\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Race\n! scope=\"col\" | 1936\n! scope=\"col\" | 1937\n! scope=\"col\" | 1938\n! scope=\"col\" | 1939\n! scope=\"col\" | 1940\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" |{{cjersey|pink}} [[General classification in the Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|'''[[1936 Giro d'Italia|9]]'''\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|'''[[1937 Giro d'Italia|3]]'''\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|'''[[1940 Giro d'Italia|2]]'''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | {{cjersey|yellow}} [[General classification in the Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| style=\"background:#ddf;\"|[[1938 Tour de France|38]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | {{cjersey|red}} [[List of Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a general classification winners|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n| \u2014\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Legend\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2014\n| Did not compete\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Did Not Finish|DNF]]\n| Did not finish\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cycling archives|6124}}\n\n{{Giro di Lombardia winners |state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mollo, Enrico}}\n[[Category:1913 births]]\n[[Category:1992 deaths]]\n[[Category:Italian male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Turin]]\n[[Category:Giro d'Italia cyclists]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n{{Italy-cycling-bio-1910s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enrico_Mollo"}
{"title_page": "Sanctify (song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name          = Sanctify\n| cover         = Years & Years Sanctify.png\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Years & Years]]\n| album         = [[Palo Santo (Years & Years album)|Palo Santo]]\n| released      = {{start date|2018|3|7|df=y}}\n| recorded      = 2017\n| format        = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| genre         = {{hlist|[[Dance music|Dance]]|[[dark pop]]|[[Pop music|pop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| length        = {{duration|m=3|s=9}}\n| label         = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| writer        = {{hlist|[[Olly Alexander]]|[[Kid Harpoon|Tom Hull]]}}\n| producer      = [[Kid Harpoon]]\n| prev_title    = [[Meteorite (Years & Years song)|Meteorite]]\n| prev_year     = 2016\n| next_title    = [[If You're Over Me]]\n| next_year     = 2018\n| misc          = {{External music video|{{YouTube|37lXjnflt9M|\"Sanctify\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Sanctify'''\" is a song recorded by British synthpop band [[Years & Years]]. Written by [[Olly Alexander]] and its producer [[Kid Harpoon]], it was released on 7 March 2018 by [[Polydor Records]], as the lead single from the band's second studio album, ''[[Palo Santo (Years & Years album)|Palo Santo]]'' (2018). It was voted as the 3rd hottest record of the year 2018 as part of [[Annie Mac]]'s hottest record of the year.<ref>{{Citation|last=BBC Radio 1|title=3  - Years & Years \u2013 Sanctify {{!}} Annie Mac's Hottest Record Of The Year 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kMWZUlHHJDg|access-date=2018-12-14}}</ref>\n\n==Release and background==\nThe band first teased the song via social media on 16 February 2018, with a cryptic video featuring a grainy footage of their \"[[King (song)|King]]\" music video as well as ideograms, leading to speculation of an upcoming announcement. They later shared another video featuring a picture of lead singer Olly Alexander that encouraged fans to sign up to their mailing list.<ref>{{cite news|last=Daly|first=Rhian|title=Years & Years return with new track 'Sanctify'|url=http://www.nme.com/news/years-and-years-return-with-new-track-sanctify-2256946|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[NME]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> Their website, which was linked in the video captions, also hinted that something was \"coming soon\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Britton|first=Luke|title=Are Years & Years set to return with new music?|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/years-years-set-return-new-music-2243595|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=NME|date=23 February 2018}}</ref> On 2 March 2018, the band posted a video which revealed the song's title and release details.<ref>{{cite news|last=Konemann|first=Liam|title=Years & Years have a new single coming out on Wednesday|url=https://www.readdork.com/news/years-years-have-a-new-single-coming-out-on-wednesday/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Dork|date=5 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]'', \"Sanctify\" was inspired by Alexander's relationship with a straight man, in which \"things became chaotic at a certain point\". He explained: \"There's so much that goes on in an experience like that. On the one hand, the guy is struggling with his sexuality and feeling unable to express himself as anything other than straight while also desiring me. I'm on the other side feeling like both a sinner and saint or a devil and angel, leading this guy down a path of 'sinfulness' while, at the same time, helping him explore his sexuality.\" The band's older songs \"have been about [Alexander] and [his] life\", but \"Sanctify\" was referred to as one of the \"more sexually overt songs\". Alexander stated that he has \"felt more empowered to be even more confessional in [his] writing\" and is \"not shying away from certain topics anymore\". He concluded by saying: \"I feel like being gay is a blessing. I wanted that to come through in the song.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Manders|first=Hayden|title=Olly Alexander On Years & Years' New Song And Hooking Up With A Straight Man|url=https://nylon.com/articles/years-and-years-sanctify-interview|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Nylon|date=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Damshenas|first=Sam|title=Years and Years' new single is about Olly Alexander's relationship with a straight man|url=http://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/101234/years-years-new-single-olly-alexanders-relationship-straight-man/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Gay Times]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Sanctify\" is a [[BDSM]]-referencing [[Dance music|dance]], [[dark pop]], [[Pop music|pop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song,<ref>Sources concerning the song's genres:\n* Dance: {{cite web|last=O'Flynn|first=Brian|title=Years & Years return from their hiatus with an unapologetic, BDSM-referencing dance track - review|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/years-and-years-sanctify-video-olly-alexander-new-album-release-date-tour-live-shows-a8245721.html|website=The Independent|date=8 March 2018|accessdate=8 July 2018}}\n* Dark pop: {{cite news|last=Gore|first=Sydney|title=Years & Years Officially Return With New Song \"Sanctify\"|url=https://www.mtv.ca/years-and-years-sanctify/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[MTV News]]|date=7 March 2018}}\n* Pop and R&B: {{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/years-and-years-palo-santo-new-album-review-olly-alexander-songs-tracklist-a8430836.html|title=Years & Years Palo Santo album review: Olly Alexander is a pop icon for this generation|website=The Independent|last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=8 July 2018}}</ref> with early 2000s pop music influences.<ref>{{cite news|last=Crowley|first=Patrick|title=Years & Years Return With Futuristic Video for 'Sanctify': Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8236301/years-and-years-sanctify-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=O'Neill|first=Lauren|title=Years & Years Are Back and Very Dystopian with New Track \"Sanctify\"|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/pam94b/years-and-years-sanctify-stream-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Noisey]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref> Alexander told [[Beats 1]]: \"Then the music side of it, I wanted something that felt like it could be [[Britney Spears|Britney]]-era '[[I'm a Slave 4 U|Slave 4 U]]' meets [[Timbaland]] or [[The Neptunes|Neptunes]]... that's my favorite kind of stuff to listen to.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Duffy|first=Nick|title=Olly Alexander: Years & Years single Sanctify is about straight guys who experiment with gay sex|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/03/09/olly-alexander-years-years-single-sanctify-is-about-straight-guys-who-experiment-with-gay-sex/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[PinkNews]]|date=9 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dommu|first=Rose|title=Olly Alexander is a Collared Boy Toy in Years & Years' 'Sanctify' Music Video|url=https://www.out.com/music/2018/3/08/olly-alexander-collared-boy-toy-years-years-sanctify-music-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Out (magazine)|Out]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref> He added in an interview with [[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]: \"When we were making it, it just sounded like a really nice blend of my favourite kind of old skool RnB, but also felt kinda fresh, so it felt like the best foot forward.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=When Is Years & Years New Album Release Date? Everything We Know About 'Sanctify' & More|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/years-and-years/news/new-album-release-date-tracklist-tour-sanctify/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Capital FM|date=7 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe accompanying music video was directed by Fred Rowson. It was situated in an imaginary future metropolis called Palo Santo, where people are captured and made to dance as a form of entertainment for androids.<ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Jamie|title=Years & Years return with new track 'Sanctify'|url=http://diymag.com/2018/03/08/years-and-years-new-track-sanctify-watch|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Wass|first=Mike|title=Years & Years Explore A Bold New Pop Sound On \"Sanctify\"|url=https://www.idolator.com/7675955/years-years-sanctify-video-review|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idoator]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> It began with Alexander being taken to an audition. At first, he is restrained by a cuff around his neck. After it releases, he dances and emotes more freely.<ref>{{cite news|last=Howard|first=Lindsay|title=Years & Years Is Free in Video for New Single 'Sanctify'|url=http://variancemagazine.com/sights/9002-years-and-years-sanctify|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Variance (magazine)|Variance]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> Alexander revealed in a press release: \"It's the first part of a bigger jigsaw puzzle and my hope is that it confuses the hell out of people but also excites them in a mysterious and sensual way. We've deliberately hidden lots of different meanings and I want people to come up with their own interpretations, I'm asking people to jump down the rabbit hole with me and let their imagination run free.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Renshaw|first=David|title=Years & Years return with new single \"Sanctify\"|url=http://www.thefader.com/2018/03/08/years-years-sancitfy|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[The Fader]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Copsey|first=Rob|title=Years and Years release new single Sanctify and unveil futuristic music video|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/years-and-years-release-new-single-sanctify-and-unveil-futuristic-music-video__22062/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nRobin Murray of ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]'' regarded the song as a piece of \"potent, poised pop music\" which \"embraces creativity as a realm for reinvention\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Robin|title=Years & Years Nail Their Colours To The Mast On 'Sanctify'|url=http://clashmusic.com/news/years-years-nail-their-colours-to-the-mast-on-sanctify|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Clash|date=8 March 2018}}</ref> Bianca Gracie of [[Fuse (TV channel)|Fuse]] felt that the song indicates \"an unexpected but thrilling sonic direction\", writing that it \"takes a much sharper turn into dark-pop territory\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|title=Years & Years Return With Electric 'Sanctify' Single: Watch The Dystopian-Themed Video|url=https://www.fuse.tv/2018/03/years-years-new-sanctify-single-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Fuse|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> Philip Cosores of ''[[Uproxx]]'' opined that it \"sounds decidedly more Justin [Bieber]\", despite Alexander's claim of Spears influences, \"but either way, the pop bona fides of the track can't be denied\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Cosores|first=Philip|title=Years & Years' 'Sanctify' Video Goes To A Sci-Fi Dystopia And Finds Humanity In Dancing|url=https://uproxx.com/music/years-and-years-sanctify/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Uproxx|date=7 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n*'''Digital download \u2013 remixes'''<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanctify (Remixes) by Years & Years|url=https://www.amazon.com/Sanctify-Remixes-Years/dp/B07CPR1LVQ|website=Amazon|accessdate=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n#\"Sanctify\" (Remix) (featuring [[Alma (Finnish singer)|ALMA]]) &nbsp;\u2013 3:10\n#\"Sanctify\" (Bernard Sumner / New Order Remix) &nbsp;\u2013 4:11\n#\"Sanctify\" (Vato Gonzalez Remix) &nbsp;\u2013 4:07\n#\"Sanctify\" (Gerd Janson Remix / Radio Edit) &nbsp;\u2013 4:10\n#\"Sanctify\" (Michael Calfan's Prayer Remix) &nbsp;\u2013 2:51\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanctify / Years & Years TIDAL|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/85371602|website=Tidal|accessdate=10 March 2018}}</ref>\n* Olly Alexander \u2013 composition, vocals\n* Kid Harpoon \u2013 composition, production\n* John Davis \u2013 master engineering\n* Michael Freeman \u2013 engineering\n* [[Spike Stent]] \u2013 mixing\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br /> position\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|47|artist=Years & Years|song=Sanctify|rowheader=true|accessdate=24 March 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|3|artist=Years & Years|song=Sanctify|rowheader=true|accessdate=6 July 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|77|year=2018|week=11|rowheader=true|accessdate=6 July 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarystream|34|year=2018|week=11|artist=Years & Years|song=Sanctify|rowheader=true|accessdate=22 March 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland3|57|artist=Years & Years|rowheader=true|accessdate=17 March 2018}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Heatseekers ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=4464|title=NZ Heatseeker Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=19 March 2018|accessdate=16 March 2018}}</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|16|date=20180406|rowheader=true|accessdate=7 April 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|25|date=20180316|rowheader=true|accessdate=17 March 2018}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboarddanceelectronic|19|artist=Years<!-- No & in the Billboard name --> Years|rowheader=true|accessdate=20 March 2018}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Years & Years}}\n\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related songs]]\n[[Category:Years & Years songs]]\n[[Category:Polydor Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Kid Harpoon]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Olly Alexander]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name          = Sanctify\n| cover         = Years & Years Sanctify.png\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Years & Years]]\n| album         = [[Palo Santo (Years & Years album)|Palo Santo]]\n| released      = {{start date|2018|3|7|df=y}}\n| recorded      = 2017\n| format        = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| genre         = {{hlist|[[Dance music|Dance]]|[[dark pop]]|[[Pop music|pop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| length        = {{duration|m=3|s=9}}\n| label         = [[Polydor Records|Polydor]]\n| writer        = {{hlist|[[Olly Alexander]]|[[Kid Harpoon|Tom Hull]]}}\n| producer      = [[Kid Harpoon]]\n| prev_title    = [[Meteorite (Years & Years song)|Meteorite]]\n| prev_year     = 2016\n| next_title    = [[If You're Over Me]]\n| next_year     = 2018\n| misc          = {{External music video|{{YouTube|37lXjnflt9M|\"Sanctify\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Sanctify'''\" is a song recorded by British synthpop band [[Years & Years]]. Written by [[Olly Alexander]] and its producer [[Kid Harpoon]], it was released on 7 March 2018 by [[Polydor Records]], as the lead single from the band's second studio album, ''[[Palo Santo (Years & Years album)|Palo Santo]]'' (2018).It was voted as the 3rd hottest record of the year 2018 as part of [[Annie Mac]]'s hottest record of the year.<ref>{{Citation|last=BBC Radio 1|title=3  - Years & Years \u2013 Sanctify {{!}} Annie Mac's Hottest Record Of The Year 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kMWZUlHHJDg|access-date=2018-12-14}}</ref>\n\n==Release and background==\nThe band first teased the song via social media on 16 February 2018, with a cryptic video featuring a grainy footage of their \"[[King (song)|King]]\" music video as well as ideograms, leading to speculation of an upcoming announcement. They later shared another video featuring a picture of lead singer Olly Alexander that encouraged fans to sign up to their mailing list.<ref>{{cite news|last=Daly|first=Rhian|title=Years & Years return with new track 'Sanctify'|url=http://www.nme.com/news/years-and-years-return-with-new-track-sanctify-2256946|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[NME]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> Their website, which was linked in the video captions, also hinted that something was \"coming soon\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Britton|first=Luke|title=Are Years & Years set to return with new music?|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/years-years-set-return-new-music-2243595|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=NME|date=23 February 2018}}</ref> On 2 March 2018, the band posted a video which revealed the song's title and release details.<ref>{{cite news|last=Konemann|first=Liam|title=Years & Years have a new single coming out on Wednesday|url=https://www.readdork.com/news/years-years-have-a-new-single-coming-out-on-wednesday/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Dork|date=5 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]'', \"Sanctify\" was inspired by Alexander's relationship with a straight man, in which \"things became chaotic at a certain point\". He explained: \"There's so much that goes on in an experience like that. On the one hand, the guy is struggling with his sexuality and feeling unable to express himself as anything other than straight while also desiring me. I'm on the other side feeling like both a sinner and saint or a devil and angel, leading this guy down a path of 'sinfulness' while, at the same time, helping him explore his sexuality.\" The band's older songs \"have been about [Alexander] and [his] life\", but \"Sanctify\" was referred to as one of the \"more sexually overt songs\". Alexander stated that he has \"felt more empowered to be even more confessional in [his] writing\" and is \"not shying away from certain topics anymore\". He concluded by saying: \"I feel like being gay is a blessing. I wanted that to come through in the song.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Manders|first=Hayden|title=Olly Alexander On Years & Years' New Song And Hooking Up With A Straight Man|url=https://nylon.com/articles/years-and-years-sanctify-interview|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Nylon|date=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Damshenas|first=Sam|title=Years and Years' new single is about Olly Alexander's relationship with a straight man|url=http://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/101234/years-years-new-single-olly-alexanders-relationship-straight-man/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Gay Times]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Sanctify\" is a [[BDSM]]-referencing [[Dance music|dance]], [[dark pop]], [[Pop music|pop]] and [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] song,<ref>Sources concerning the song's genres:\n* Dance: {{cite web|last=O'Flynn|first=Brian|title=Years & Years return from their hiatus with an unapologetic, BDSM-referencing dance track - review|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/years-and-years-sanctify-video-olly-alexander-new-album-release-date-tour-live-shows-a8245721.html|website=The Independent|date=8 March 2018|accessdate=8 July 2018}}\n* Dark pop: {{cite news|last=Gore|first=Sydney|title=Years & Years Officially Return With New Song \"Sanctify\"|url=https://www.mtv.ca/years-and-years-sanctify/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[MTV News]]|date=7 March 2018}}\n* Pop and R&B: {{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/years-and-years-palo-santo-new-album-review-olly-alexander-songs-tracklist-a8430836.html|title=Years & Years Palo Santo album review: Olly Alexander is a pop icon for this generation|website=The Independent|last=O'Connor|first=Roisin|date=5 July 2018|accessdate=8 July 2018}}</ref> with early 2000s pop music influences.<ref>{{cite news|last=Crowley|first=Patrick|title=Years & Years Return With Futuristic Video for 'Sanctify': Watch|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/pride/8236301/years-and-years-sanctify-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=O'Neill|first=Lauren|title=Years & Years Are Back and Very Dystopian with New Track \"Sanctify\"|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/pam94b/years-and-years-sanctify-stream-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Noisey]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref> Alexander told [[Beats 1]]: \"Then the music side of it, I wanted something that felt like it could be [[Britney Spears|Britney]]-era '[[I'm a Slave 4 U|Slave 4 U]]' meets [[Timbaland]] or [[The Neptunes|Neptunes]]... that's my favorite kind of stuff to listen to.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Duffy|first=Nick|title=Olly Alexander: Years & Years single Sanctify is about straight guys who experiment with gay sex|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2018/03/09/olly-alexander-years-years-single-sanctify-is-about-straight-guys-who-experiment-with-gay-sex/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[PinkNews]]|date=9 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dommu|first=Rose|title=Olly Alexander is a Collared Boy Toy in Years & Years' 'Sanctify' Music Video|url=https://www.out.com/music/2018/3/08/olly-alexander-collared-boy-toy-years-years-sanctify-music-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Out (magazine)|Out]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref> He added in an interview with [[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]: \"When we were making it, it just sounded like a really nice blend of my favourite kind of old skool RnB, but also felt kinda fresh, so it felt like the best foot forward.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=When Is Years & Years New Album Release Date? Everything We Know About 'Sanctify' & More|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/years-and-years/news/new-album-release-date-tracklist-tour-sanctify/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Capital FM|date=7 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe accompanying music video was directed by Fred Rowson. It was situated in an imaginary future metropolis called Palo Santo, where people are captured and made to dance as a form of entertainment for androids.<ref>{{cite news|last=Miller|first=Jamie|title=Years & Years return with new track 'Sanctify'|url=http://diymag.com/2018/03/08/years-and-years-new-track-sanctify-watch|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Wass|first=Mike|title=Years & Years Explore A Bold New Pop Sound On \"Sanctify\"|url=https://www.idolator.com/7675955/years-years-sanctify-video-review|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idoator]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> It began with Alexander being taken to an audition. At first, he is restrained by a cuff around his neck. After it releases, he dances and emotes more freely.<ref>{{cite news|last=Howard|first=Lindsay|title=Years & Years Is Free in Video for New Single 'Sanctify'|url=http://variancemagazine.com/sights/9002-years-and-years-sanctify|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Variance (magazine)|Variance]]|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> Alexander revealed in a press release: \"It's the first part of a bigger jigsaw puzzle and my hope is that it confuses the hell out of people but also excites them in a mysterious and sensual way. We've deliberately hidden lots of different meanings and I want people to come up with their own interpretations, I'm asking people to jump down the rabbit hole with me and let their imagination run free.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Renshaw|first=David|title=Years & Years return with new single \"Sanctify\"|url=http://www.thefader.com/2018/03/08/years-years-sancitfy|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[The Fader]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Copsey|first=Rob|title=Years and Years release new single Sanctify and unveil futuristic music video|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/years-and-years-release-new-single-sanctify-and-unveil-futuristic-music-video__22062/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[Official Charts Company]]|date=8 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nRobin Murray of ''[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]'' regarded the song as a piece of \"potent, poised pop music\" which \"embraces creativity as a realm for reinvention\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Murray|first=Robin|title=Years & Years Nail Their Colours To The Mast On 'Sanctify'|url=http://clashmusic.com/news/years-years-nail-their-colours-to-the-mast-on-sanctify|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Clash|date=8 March 2018}}</ref> Bianca Gracie of [[Fuse (TV channel)|Fuse]] felt that the song indicates \"an unexpected but thrilling sonic direction\", writing that it \"takes a much sharper turn into dark-pop territory\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Gracie|first=Bianca|title=Years & Years Return With Electric 'Sanctify' Single: Watch The Dystopian-Themed Video|url=https://www.fuse.tv/2018/03/years-years-new-sanctify-single-video|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Fuse|date=7 March 2018}}</ref> Philip Cosores of ''[[Uproxx]]'' opined that it \"sounds decidedly more Justin [Bieber]\", despite Alexander's claim of Spears influences, \"but either way, the pop bona fides of the track can't be denied\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Cosores|first=Philip|title=Years & Years' 'Sanctify' Video Goes To A Sci-Fi Dystopia And Finds Humanity In Dancing|url=https://uproxx.com/music/years-and-years-sanctify/|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=Uproxx|date=7 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n*'''Digital download \u2013 remixes'''<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanctify (Remixes) by Years & Years|url=https://www.amazon.com/Sanctify-Remixes-Years/dp/B07CPR1LVQ|website=Amazon|accessdate=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n#\"Sanctify\" (Remix) (featuring [[Alma (Finnish singer)|ALMA]]) &nbsp;\u2013 3:10\n#\"Sanctify\" (Bernard Sumner / New Order Remix) &nbsp;\u2013 4:11\n#\"Sanctify\" (Vato Gonzalez Remix) &nbsp;\u2013 4:07\n#\"Sanctify\" (Gerd Janson Remix / Radio Edit) &nbsp;\u2013 4:10\n#\"Sanctify\" (Michael Calfan's Prayer Remix) &nbsp;\u2013 2:51\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sanctify / Years & Years TIDAL|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/85371602|website=Tidal|accessdate=10 March 2018}}</ref>\n* Olly Alexander \u2013 composition, vocals\n* Kid Harpoon \u2013 composition, production\n* John Davis \u2013 master engineering\n* Michael Freeman \u2013 engineering\n* [[Spike Stent]] \u2013 mixing\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\